title: HOPR Token Proposal Vote
body:
### **How should the 485,355 HOPR tokens generated from the Balancer Liquidity Pool and the Uniswap v2 pool be used?**

After a week of [discussion and signature gathering](https://forum.hoprnet.org/c/hopr-dao-v0-2/hopr-token-proposals/65), five of the original eight proposals suggested by the HOPR Association reached the 15% threshold needed to progress to a vote.

Click any of the proposal titles below to read a proposal in full. Please read all the proposals and then vote for your favourite. Your voting power is equal to the HOPR tokens controlled by your connected address (including HOPR, xHOPR, wxHOPR and xHOPR in our staking program, but not tokens in CEXs or liquidity pools).

You can assign your voting power however you like, among any number of options. **Each HOPR token equals one vote.**

Once the vote is over, the four proposals which receive the most support will be implemented, with the budget split 40/30/20/10.

The five proposals are:

- PROPOSAL #2: [Hackathons (live or online) in 2022](https://forum.hoprnet.org/t/proposal-2-hackathons-live-or-online-in-2022/3100)

- PROPOSAL #3: [Grow the HOPR Hardware Node Network](https://forum.hoprnet.org/t/proposal-3-grow-the-hopr-hardware-node-network/3102)

- PROPOSAL #4: [Liquidity Incentives](https://forum.hoprnet.org/t/proposal-4-liquidity-incentives/3103/)

- PROPOSAL #5: [Online Marketing](https://forum.hoprnet.org/t/proposal-5-online-marketing/3104)

- PROPOSAL #7: [Local Community Funds](https://forum.hoprnet.org/t/proposal-7-local-community-funds/3106)
